                        <span class="heading-cap">History </span>The
                        concept of everyday beauty was one of the starting points for developing ARKET as well as a
                        major influence on the Nordic modernist movement in the mid-20th century. Formulated in 1919 by
                        Swedish art historian Gregor Paulsson, ‘More beautiful everyday things’ became the slogan for a
                        new democratic approach that aimed to bridge the worlds of arts, crafts and functional form to
                        produce affordable and widely accessible items for everyday use.</h2></div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-container">
